devdoc.details: | A reference contract related to the Trust Channel Managers's routing contract, used for externally coordinating trusted asset flows. | An example call within the Shyft Core Contracts architecture is within the ShyftCacheGraph.sol contract, which implements an asset flow.

constructor.details: Initializes this contract with the owner set to the calling public address.

getExternalTrustLevel(uint32,address,add.details: | An internal function to function generates the relative trust level of the counterparties in relation to all of the Rules set for this Trust Channel. This function checks for a Verification Policy, Amount Limits per transaction, and also enables external checks (defined by the Multisig administrators to the Trust Channel) via an other smart contract address.      | Externally referenced smart contracts have the same input/output types as defined in the "getExternalTrustLevel" function.

params._bip32X_type: the token type that is being transmitted
params._requiredActive: whether an "active" status is required from the channel
params._requiredConsentFromAllParties: whether "consented" status is required from all parties
params._trustChannelIndex: the Index for the Trust Channel this calculation is referencing

returns.externalTrustLevel: the external trust level of the counterparties in respect to the trust channel's routing rules
returns.success: whether the external trust level returns success

getRelativeTrustLevelOnlyClean(address,a.details: | This function gets the relative KYC level on a transactional basis between two counterparties. Included in the checks are the baseline information that is needed to determine counterparty conditions.      | The other method of calling this function include parameters useful in an "Assured Asset" profile.

params._bip32X_type: the token type that is being transmitted
params._requiredActive: whether an "active" status is required from the channel
params._requiredConsentFromAllParties: whether "consented" status is required from all parties

returns.externalTrustLevel: the external trust level of the counterparties
returns.relativeTrustLevel: the relative trust level of the counterparties

setShyftCacheGraphAddress(address).details: Links the Shyft Cache Graph to this contract's function flow.

params._shyftCacheGraphAddress: The smart contract address for the Shyft Cache Graph that should be linked.

returns.result: | false: [ will never return false due to require() ]    | true: shyft cache graph address set correctly

setTrustChannelManagerAddress(address).details: Links Trust Channel Manager to this contract's function flow.

params._trustChannelManagerAddress: The smart contract address for the Trust Channel Manager that should be linked.

returns.result: | false: [ will never return false due to require() ]    | true: trust channel manager address set correctly

shyftCacheGraphAddress.details: The Shyft Cache Graph address that this contract is bound to.

trustChannelManagerAddress.details: The Trust Anchor Manager address that this contract is bound to.
